<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 3:39PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Mason,
north central Kanawha, northern Putnam, northwestern Roane and
Jackson Counties through 415 PM EDT...
At 338 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ripley, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ripley, Winfield, Sissonville, Eleanor, Buffalo, Kenna, Bancroft,
Statts Mills, Given, Kentuck, Liberty, Cottageville, Evans, Fraziers
Bottom, Leroy, Fairplain, Gay and Grimms Landing.
This includes Interstate 77 in West Virginia between mile markers 114
and 142.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
